# Docker/build files must stay LF. With core.autocrlf=true a re-checkout would otherwise flip these
# to CRLF, which (a) breaks .dockerignore pattern matching — the build then copies the host
# node_modules/.venv and the frontend build fails on the wrong-platform binaries — and (b) breaks the
# shell CMD line. Scoped to the build files; the rest of the repo keeps its current behavior.
Dockerfile         text eol=lf
.dockerignore      text eol=lf
docker-compose.yml text eol=lf
*.conf             text eol=lf

# The externalized LLM system prompts (refactor S3) stay LF so the bytes the model sees are stable across
# platforms. The loader also normalizes newlines at read time (belt + suspenders); the golden-hash test pins
# the model-visible bytes regardless, but eol=lf keeps the committed file clean.
backend/llm/prompts/*.md text eol=lf
